QUEEN IS COMING. February 28th 2020. Queen Sono, Netflix's first African Original. JOHANNESBURG - Queen Sono, the first original African series will officially premiere on 28 February 2020. Netflix South Africa announced the premiere date with a short clip featuring Pearl Thusi, who plays the lead character in the series. Queen Sono: SA's first Netflix original series "PEARL THUSI AS QUEEN SONO!!!! WHAT!!!????? THANK YOU GOD!!!! THANK YOU!!! I LIFT YOUR NAME!!! THANK YOU TO MY ANCESTORS!!! THANK YOU TO MY FAMILY!!! OH HOW I WISH MY MOM WAS HERE!!!!", said Thusi in a post on Instagram. The six-part series is directed by South African comedian Kagiso Lediga with Tamsin Andersson as the co-executive producer. “TAKE UP SPACE !!! “ @zozitunzi ✊🏾 . PEARL THUSI AS QUEEN SONO!!!! WHAT!!!????? THANK YOU GOD!!!! THANK YOU!!! I LIFT YOUR NAME!!! THANK YOU TO MY ANCESTORS!!! THANK YOU TO MY FAMILY!!! OH HOW I WISH MY MOM WAS HERE!!!! 😭😭😭😭👑👑👑👑🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽 A post shared by  Pearl Thusi (@pearlthusi) on Dec 10, 2019 at 12:41am PST